The sacred waters of this fountain enable resting.

Tumble
Any build that lacks access to tumble now gains +2 deflection ac. (A Barbarian/Ranger/WM would now receive +2 deflection ac)

General Otman
The minotaur boss will now drop a ring used in DM events. You will lose the ring if another player kills you (they will now control the ring).

Faction XP
Exploit/Bug fixed
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Champion of Torm
"Higher devotion to Torm has great costs, but even greater rewards for the Champions of this deity. Through constant adherence to their holy code of honor and their passion for the removal of corruption, Champions of Torm can become efficient tools of destruction, at the cost of their own personal safety and defense."

Divine Wrath changes: 
-Removed all save bonuses
-Added will save decrease (equivalent to 1 + 1 per 5 CoT levels)
-AC Penalty: -1 per 5 CoT levels
-Elemental Damage Vulnerability (a percent equal to CoT level)
-Divine Damage Bonus (an increase of +5 to all levels)
-Duration Increase (an additional 30 seconds per use)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ranger
"Epic rangers become a flurry of death while dual-wielding or wielding large weapons of devastation."

Altered dual-wielding and using two-handed weapons for skilled rangers (requires: ranger lvl 9+, character lvl 20+)
-If strength is 22 or greater and dual-wielding, gain +1 APR and +3 Shield AC (Stacks with old dual-wield bonus, max +8 shield ac)
-Two-handers gain +1 apr, +2 ac
-If strength is less than 22, gain +1 APR and +1 Shield AC (Stacks, max +6 shield ac)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Fighter
Fighter Dodge: -1 ac if your character has paladin levels

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Weapon Master
"Epic weapon masters can swing their weapons with such power and speed that the sound alone has been known to kill lesser foes." (Sorry if that was lame, I just needed to fit sonic damage in lore-wise somehow)
-Bonus sonic damage equivalent to the weapon master superior weapon attack bonus (SWAB).
-If str is more than 21: AC increase equivalent to SWAB. Removed if 16+ fighter lvls present.
-If str is less than 22: AC and Disc increased, based on SWAB (AC caps at +2, disc bonus equal to SWAB-2)
-AB increases at lvl 13 and 28.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Assassin
All assassin spells have been altered. The feats "epic improved sneak attack" modify most of the spells. All spells are subject to spell failure and counter, although you shouldn't lose any uses if this happens. The cast range on all spells remains the same.

Ghostly Visage: Old bonuses removed, now gives +1 Ab/Disc at lvls 20, 25. Added Conceal equal to Assn level + 10. Lasts until death/rest.

Invisibility: "Mark Target" - Can now only be cast on hostile targets. Unlimited uses, 40 second cooldown. 
-Target receives -1 ac penalty per 6 levels of assassin
-Effect lasts 3 rounds
-After 3 rounds, the mark explodes dealing 15 + Assassin level + (6 times the number of epic sneak feats).
-Cooldown reduced by 2 second per epic sneak feat taken.

Improved Invisibity: "Assassinate" - Can now only be cast on hostile targets. Unlimited uses, 60 second cooldown.
-Damages the target for: 20 + (2 * assain levels) + (8 * epic sneak feats)
-If target survives, their body is weakened and they receive -2 fortitude for 60 seconds. Does not stack with itself.
-Cooldown reduced by 4 seconds per epic sneak feat taken.

Darkness: A bunch of deadly assassin friends of yours strike in the darkness, dealing damage or even killing weakened foes. (It works similar to PWKill).
-If enemies in the targeted area have low health they are killed (Target health must be less than 40 + [2 * assn level] + [10 * epic sneak feats taken])
-If the target survives, it takes damage: 20 + Assassin level
-Cooldown of 60 seconds

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Blackguard
Blackguard bull strength now has one use and recharges every 60 seconds (can be used every minute)

The bull str buff will last for three minutes and will remove the previous bonuses each use (no stacking). Enemies within range of the BG using bull strength will grant:
-Enemies with less than 20% health give +4 ab
-Enemies with less than 60% health give +3 ab
-Enemies with less than 90% health give +2 ab

Minimum AB has been increased to +2 for builds with 10 or more BG (previously 1).
Epic BGs will now receive +1 to the max ab calculation every four lvls (previously 3/lvl).
-Max AB = 1 with low level BG, 2 at lvl 10, and +1 every four levels after 10.
-Min AB = 1 with low level BG and 2 with ten levels of BG.

The feat Epic Fiendish Servant now grants +1 to the min and max AB calculation, and damages all enemies hit. 
Any enemy hit will now grant at least +2 ab to the BG, regardless of enemy health (that is, the percent threshold increases from 90% to 100%).
-Damage equivalent to the max ab the BG can attain multiplied by 8.

Epic Reputation: "Your vile reputation emanates corruption into the very soil you walk on. Nearby enemies can be corrupted upon a flick of your wrist."
-Your Bull Strength ability decreases your saves by 1 due to your evil nature, but will also decrease the saves of enemies by 1 and their skills by 3. 
-Lasts five rounds at level 10, and one additional round every four BG lvls after (Epic Fiendish servant adds +1 round). Lasts Four rounds if < 10 BG.
